   "source": [
    "We generated the modified preferential attachment network with the given parameters. In this model, a node’s probability of getting new edges depends on both its degree and its age. Since β = −1, older nodes are penalized, so they are less likely to keep attracting edges over time. From the degree distribution plot, the network is still heavy-tailed. The log-log plot looks roughly linear over part of the range, which suggests power-law behavior. Based on the fitted line, the estimated power-law exponent is about 2.59. Compared with standard preferential attachment, the age penalty reduces the advantage of very old nodes, so the distribution is still heavy-tailed but less dominated by the earliest nodes."
   ]
